      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The premier Gollan barn may hold the aces.  LUCKY LASS (5) raced forward at Ipswich second-up and looked a run short beaten 2.4L. She has plenty up her sleeve and the longer sprint suits. Has been kept on the fresh side and has the inside barrier. Stablemate MAYBE (4) also presents third-up off solid placings in stronger. Has a small claim and plenty of gate speed. She should be right in it. HAPPY WINS (8) is an improver in a leading city stable. Led and won a Maiden by a big space at Kilcoy first-up and then fronted up there again at short quote and couldn't quite get the job done. Presents fitter and she also has winning claims. EXOFLOW (3) was narrowly beaten at Ipswich at his lone start last preparation. Wasn't beaten far in a recent trial at the Gold Coast and it won't surprise to see him race well.",
